Below is the UX-10 full patch pack.

UX-10 goal

Make the result experience feel product-grade, not transitional.

This phase focuses on:

result pane visual polish,
stable transitions,
“why these results” clarity,
side-by-side person comparison,
better no-result / loading / onboarding experiences,
stronger review workflows around people,
cleaner search-to-result continuity.

This is the phase where the app starts feeling closer to Google Photos / Apple Photos / Lightroom / Excire in day-to-day use.

UX-10 scope

This pack includes six sub-phases:

UX-10A, Result pane structure polish
dedicated result explanation area
stable loading and empty-state switching
clearer result count and sort behavior
UX-10B, Side-by-side person comparison UI
visual comparison dialog for merge review
representative face strip
merge / reject actions
UX-10C, Unnamed-cluster review workflow
open unnamed-cluster review
assign to existing person
keep separate
ignore
UX-10D, Facet quality refinement
cleaner visible facet logic
stronger people facet exposure
stable browse/search interaction
UX-10E, Activity visibility polish
mini activity strip quality improvements
connect mini activity and full activity center more cleanly
UX-10F, Result continuity and review ergonomics
preserve selection where possible
smoother result refresh behavior
review-state-safe refreshes
